243
00:18:21,767 --> 00:18:25,395
[scoffs] I am not
interested in excuses, Toby.

244
00:18:26,980 --> 00:18:28,982
I'm sorry, Lord Karuku.

245
00:18:30,109 --> 00:18:34,238
Well, you will just have
to work harder, won't you?

246
00:18:34,571 --> 00:18:38,826
Because I simply have to have
my living puppets, don't I?

247
00:18:38,867 --> 00:18:42,454
-Yes Master.
-Oh yes, Toby,

248
00:18:43,288 --> 00:18:46,083
once you're finished
with all the animals,

249
00:18:46,291 --> 00:18:50,796
you may begin collecting... people.

250
00:18:52,047 --> 00:18:53,841
Collecting people?

251
00:18:54,466 --> 00:18:56,760
I believe that's what I said.

252
00:18:57,344 --> 00:18:59,429
They are such stupid things,

253
00:19:00,222 --> 00:19:04,059
that I am sure they'll be even
easier for you to deal with

254
00:19:04,059 --> 00:19:05,269
than the animals.

255
00:19:05,477 --> 00:19:09,398
You may begin with those houses
down in the valley there.

256
00:19:09,773 --> 00:19:12,484
You'd do that for me, won't you?

257
00:19:14,695 --> 00:19:18,115
-Toby?
-I will of course, Master.

258
00:19:18,240 --> 00:19:20,576
And in return you will teach
me more of your magic?

259
00:19:21,702 --> 00:19:25,455
Hurry up and bring the living
puppets to my island.

260
00:19:25,581 --> 00:19:29,168
And if I am pleased, I suppose
I might teach you another

261
00:19:29,168 --> 00:19:32,045
-magic trick.
-[Toby] Master.

262
00:19:32,963 --> 00:19:35,132
And be quick about it too, Toby.

263
00:19:35,382 --> 00:19:36,925
Yes, Lord Karuku.

264
00:19:38,427 --> 00:19:39,428
[electronic whizzing]

265
00:19:42,556 --> 00:19:45,058
[stuttering] What was that?

266
00:19:45,642 --> 00:19:46,768
A magician.

267
00:19:47,436 --> 00:19:48,687
And my master.

268
00:19:49,021 --> 00:19:52,232
That's some trick appearing
and disappearing like that.

269
00:19:53,275 --> 00:19:56,195
Did he say he wanted
you to start turning people

270
00:19:56,195 --> 00:19:59,907
into living puppets? Ha,
that's my idea of a good time.

271
00:19:59,990 --> 00:20:03,160
I never liked people,
can't stand 'em, come on,

272
00:20:03,202 --> 00:20:08,207
zap 'em. Oh boy, I can't
wait to see this, ha.

273
00:20:08,248 --> 00:20:12,461
Be quiet, unless you want
to be the very first to undergo

274
00:20:12,502 --> 00:20:15,297
-the transformation.
-[trembling sighs]

275
00:20:15,756 --> 00:20:17,841
This wasn't part of the bargain.

276
00:20:18,800 --> 00:20:22,054
[Melvin] Say, are you really
gonna zap every one

277
00:20:22,054 --> 00:20:24,348
of the people down there?
Every one? [cries]

278
00:20:24,348 --> 00:20:26,266
-I said be quiet.
-Sorry.

279
00:20:38,111 --> 00:20:40,614
[Sherry] Huh, he's awake.

280
00:20:40,906 --> 00:20:42,574
It's amazing he's still alive

281
00:20:42,574 --> 00:20:44,534
after all that he's
been through.

282
00:20:44,785 --> 00:20:46,453
[giggles] Isn't he cute?

283
00:20:46,828 --> 00:20:49,456
Are you alright? Huh?

284
00:20:50,374 --> 00:20:52,584
It looks like somebody
ruffed the little fellow up.

285
00:20:52,751 --> 00:20:54,586
Here you go, drink some milk.

286
00:20:55,712 --> 00:20:58,423
[father] I can't say I've ever
seen anything quite like him.

287
00:20:59,633 --> 00:21:02,052
Here, you gotta have
some of this milk.

288
00:21:02,511 --> 00:21:04,137
That way you'll get
your strength back.

289
00:21:04,388 --> 00:21:05,389
Come on.

290
00:21:06,181 --> 00:21:09,101
Here, watch me and I'll show
you how to do it, alright?

291
00:21:11,144 --> 00:21:13,438
[scoffs] He's probably
frightened of people.

292
00:21:13,981 --> 00:21:15,482
Well, I'll take care of that.

293
00:21:15,941 --> 00:21:18,193
You see that man at the table
smoking a pipe?

294
00:21:18,527 --> 00:21:19,945
That man is my father.

295
00:21:20,195 --> 00:21:23,365
And that woman with her hands
in the suds is my mother.

296
00:21:24,408 --> 00:21:25,575
Is it working?

297
00:21:26,868 --> 00:21:28,912
[sighs] There you go.

298
00:21:31,331 --> 00:21:34,334
There used to be another
person here, my older brother.

299
00:21:34,751 --> 00:21:35,919
But he went away.

300
00:21:36,378 --> 00:21:38,547
That was almost
three years ago now.

301
00:21:39,965 --> 00:21:42,718
I wonder where he is,
what he's doing.

302
00:21:42,843 --> 00:21:45,012
It's time we forgot about him.

303
00:21:45,554 --> 00:21:49,766
Enough! I'm certain he's
forgotten all about us by now.

304
00:21:52,519 --> 00:21:54,604
I have an early day,
I'm turning in.

305
00:21:59,109 --> 00:22:01,778
-Goodnight, Father.
-[sighs]

306
00:22:03,739 --> 00:22:04,740
[Mother] Goodnight.

307
00:22:11,955 --> 00:22:15,667
Why do I make Father angry
whenever I mention my brother?

308
00:22:17,502 --> 00:22:19,921
Your father's not angry
with you, dear.

309
00:22:20,630 --> 00:22:23,175
When a man is worried
by something inside him,

310
00:22:23,342 --> 00:22:25,761
and he's too proud
to weep or cry out,

311
00:22:26,011 --> 00:22:28,805
he sometimes gets angry
at those around him.

312
00:22:29,306 --> 00:22:33,268
But he's not angry with you,
not with you.

313
00:22:35,354 --> 00:22:37,898
Poor little fellow, you look
like you haven't a friend

314
00:22:37,939 --> 00:22:38,982
in the world.

315
00:22:40,150 --> 00:22:41,151
Me too.

316
00:22:41,568 --> 00:22:44,154
I lost my best friend
when I lost my brother.

317
00:22:46,782 --> 00:22:47,949
Don't be frightened.

318
00:22:48,658 --> 00:22:51,787
From now on, we can be
each other's best friend.

319
00:22:52,245 --> 00:22:53,747
Isn't that right, Mother?

320
00:22:54,206 --> 00:22:55,582
[Mother] That's right, Sherry.

321
00:22:56,500 --> 00:22:58,960
So, let's have
a little milk now.

322
00:23:00,212 --> 00:23:02,297
Come on, what's wrong with you?

323
00:23:02,631 --> 00:23:04,257
You've got to drink some.

324
00:23:04,508 --> 00:23:07,427
Sherry, don't threaten him,
you're just frightening him

325
00:23:07,469 --> 00:23:08,637
all the more.

326
00:23:09,638 --> 00:23:11,473
[giggles] Sorry.

327
00:23:12,682 --> 00:23:14,434
He'll be better in the morning.

328
00:23:16,144 --> 00:23:17,896
Come along, it's time for bed.

329
00:23:18,271 --> 00:23:19,815
-Mother?
-Yes Dear?

330
00:23:19,856 --> 00:23:22,067
May I stay up with him
a little longer?

331
00:23:22,442 --> 00:23:26,029
-Alright, don't be too long.
-I won't. Goodnight.

332
00:23:29,783 --> 00:23:31,451
I like you, you know.

333
00:23:34,329 --> 00:23:35,664
I like all animals.

334
00:23:36,581 --> 00:23:40,794
Birds and rabbits,
and squirrels and everything.

335
00:23:41,753 --> 00:23:45,215
And I like... my brother.

336
00:23:45,799 --> 00:23:47,509
I like him a lot.

337
00:23:51,012 --> 00:23:53,640
I'm... Unico.

338
00:24:04,443 --> 00:24:05,444
[birds tweeting]

339
00:24:13,243 --> 00:24:14,911
[Sherry] I like all animals.

340
00:24:15,287 --> 00:24:17,414
Birds and rabbits,
and everything.

341
00:24:17,956 --> 00:24:20,917
And I like you too.
[sighs]

342
00:24:21,793 --> 00:24:24,546
[gentle sigh]

343
00:24:30,260 --> 00:24:34,139
[gasps] So you're not afraid
of me anymore, are you?

344
00:24:34,139 --> 00:24:37,517
-I'm Unico.
-[gasps] Unico?

345
00:24:38,477 --> 00:24:42,105
[Sherry yells] Mother? Father?
The little one is all better.

346
00:24:42,355 --> 00:24:45,358
Come on, I'll race
you to the bridge.

347
00:24:45,650 --> 00:24:48,612
-Faster, Unico. Faster. [laughs]
-[giggling]

348
00:24:49,362 --> 00:24:50,363
Come on!

349
00:24:50,947 --> 00:24:54,451
Here, we're friends now, we
must swear eternal friendship,

350
00:24:54,493 --> 00:24:57,245
so no matter what happens
we'll stand by each other.

351
00:24:57,537 --> 00:24:58,580
Let's shake hands.

352
00:24:59,247 --> 00:25:01,041
-Come on!
-Okay.

353
00:25:02,959 --> 00:25:05,629
-[Unico giggling] Wait for me.
-Come on.

354
00:25:07,422 --> 00:25:09,508
-[Unico] Where are you?
-I'm over here.

355
00:25:10,550 --> 00:25:11,927
There you are.

356
00:25:17,891 --> 00:25:18,892
[thunder]

357
00:25:22,938 --> 00:25:25,857
Sherry? Come on
into the house now.

358
00:25:26,024 --> 00:25:27,692
It looks like it's
going to rain.

359
00:25:27,859 --> 00:25:29,110
Come on now.

360
00:25:30,737 --> 00:25:31,738
[lightening cracks]

361
00:25:33,532 --> 00:25:34,533
[trembling]

362
00:25:37,953 --> 00:25:40,497
Don't worry, there's nothing
to be frightened of.

363
00:25:40,747 --> 00:25:42,791
I thought you were
a brave little fella.

364
00:25:43,041 --> 00:25:46,795
Just repeat, \"I'm not scared,\"
three times and you'll be fine.

365
00:25:47,337 --> 00:25:50,507
[loud gasp] I guess
it is a little scary.

366
00:25:51,841 --> 00:25:52,842
-Hm?
-Huh?

367
00:25:53,176 --> 00:25:54,177
[creaking]

368
00:25:58,974 --> 00:25:59,975
[wind howls]

369
00:26:02,018 --> 00:26:04,896
Ja, ja. [laughs]

370
00:26:08,024 --> 00:26:09,317
What is it you want?

371
00:26:14,197 --> 00:26:17,367
It's my big brother,
he's come home.

372
00:26:17,993 --> 00:26:22,330
-[stutters] Toby, is that you?
-Oh, yes, it is you!

373
00:26:22,497 --> 00:26:24,416
You've come home at last.

374
00:26:24,624 --> 00:26:26,626
[Sherry] So where have
you been all this time?

375
00:26:26,751 --> 00:26:29,796
-We were so worried about you.
-[Mother] Oh, Toby.

376
00:26:30,046 --> 00:26:33,049
But my boy, what on earth
is that you've got on?

377
00:26:33,049 --> 00:26:35,885
It looks like
a magician's costume, Toby?

378
00:26:36,636 --> 00:26:38,471
That's exactly
what it is, Mother.

379
00:26:38,763 --> 00:26:40,599
Hm?
[electronic beeps]

380
00:26:42,058 --> 00:26:43,727
-[gasps]
-Huh?

381
00:26:45,854 --> 00:26:50,317
Oh no, that terrible man
is Sherry's lost brother.

382
00:26:51,943 --> 00:26:53,653
[sniffing]
[fire crackling]

383
00:26:55,363 --> 00:26:57,532
This smells kind of familiar.

384
00:26:57,782 --> 00:26:58,783
Hm.

385
00:27:00,785 --> 00:27:02,704
[Toby] Sherry,
I've brought you a gift.

386
00:27:06,875 --> 00:27:07,876
[sniffing continues]

387
00:27:09,669 --> 00:27:10,670
Hm.

388
00:27:12,339 --> 00:27:13,465
-Hm, hm.
-Oh.

389
00:27:15,634 --> 00:27:17,469
Watch closely now.

390
00:27:22,349 --> 00:27:24,684
Isn't it the loveliest doll
you've ever seen?

391
00:27:25,352 --> 00:27:29,606
-Take it, it's yours?
-I can't, I'm afraid of it.

392
00:27:31,024 --> 00:27:34,194
And after I went to all
the trouble of making for you.

393
00:27:34,778 --> 00:27:35,779
[scoffs]

394
00:27:40,325 --> 00:27:41,326
[scoffs]

395
00:27:42,243 --> 00:27:46,164
-Toby, what have you become?
-What you see, Father.

396
00:27:46,873 --> 00:27:49,668
I can do anything.
[electronic tinkling]

397
00:27:50,502 --> 00:27:51,503
Hm?

398
00:27:52,712 --> 00:27:55,548
Toby, stop it,
leave your father alone.

399
00:27:59,010 --> 00:28:02,138
-I don't like this, my boy.
-From this moment on,

400
00:28:02,222 --> 00:28:05,141
you will wear nothing but
the finest dresses, Mother.

401
00:28:05,642 --> 00:28:07,894
[electronic zapping]
[loud gasp]

402
00:28:10,814 --> 00:28:14,651
I don't want them, I don't
want them, leave me alone!

403
00:28:14,651 --> 00:28:16,194
What are you trying
to do, Toby?

404
00:28:16,361 --> 00:28:17,362
I can do anything.

405
00:28:17,904 --> 00:28:19,030
Anything at all.

406
00:28:20,907 --> 00:28:23,993
I have been given the power
to make you all happy

407
00:28:24,035 --> 00:28:25,328
for the rest of your lives.

408
00:28:26,121 --> 00:28:29,582
Father, that old pipe is your
prized possession, isn't it?

409
00:28:30,792 --> 00:28:32,711
Well, I can turn
that pipe into gold.

410
00:28:32,836 --> 00:28:33,837
Stop it!

411
00:28:34,087 --> 00:28:37,382
These powers of yours, they're,
they're not right, Toby.

412
00:28:38,508 --> 00:28:41,302
You can't find real happiness
by waving your hand,

413
00:28:41,302 --> 00:28:43,096
and casting a magic spell.

414
00:28:43,805 --> 00:28:47,726
[sighs] I should've know
you'd say something like that.

415
00:28:48,560 --> 00:28:50,520
You haven't changed
a bit, Father.

416
00:28:51,730 --> 00:28:52,689
Hm, oh.

417
00:28:54,190 --> 00:28:57,277
Ah-ha! I knew it had to be you!
I knew it.

418
00:28:57,277 --> 00:29:00,655
I knew it all the time.
Now I got you! [laughs]

419
00:29:01,281 --> 00:29:02,240
Shh.

420
00:29:03,450 --> 00:29:04,492
Hm?

421
00:29:05,243 --> 00:29:06,244
[Toby blows]

422
00:29:09,789 --> 00:29:14,294
[Karuku] Toby? Toby?

423
00:29:14,335 --> 00:29:16,838
Mother, Father, Sherry!
You've got to hide.

424
00:29:16,963 --> 00:29:18,173
Get out of here!

425
00:29:18,298 --> 00:29:20,341
Ridiculous! This is our home,

426
00:29:20,341 --> 00:29:22,469
what on earth should
we hide from?

427
00:29:23,470 --> 00:29:25,430
-There's no time to explain--
-[Karuku] Toby?

428
00:29:25,930 --> 00:29:28,349
-[gasping]
-Toby.

429
00:29:29,559 --> 00:29:34,731
Toby, you're not being
lazy again, are you?

430
00:29:35,273 --> 00:29:38,526
Toby! Toby!

431
00:29:39,110 --> 00:29:44,324
My, my, Toby, imagine finding
you in a place like this?

432
00:29:45,784 --> 00:29:49,204
Oh, those are people,
aren't they, Toby?

433
00:29:49,245 --> 00:29:52,207
No, Lord Karuku,
these people are useless.

434
00:29:52,832 --> 00:29:55,168
Oh Toby, you do
them a disservice,

435
00:29:55,168 --> 00:29:57,670
I think they will make
delightful puppets.

436
00:29:58,713 --> 00:29:59,714
[both groaning]

437
00:30:01,800 --> 00:30:02,801
[thuds]

438
00:30:05,220 --> 00:30:09,307
Now, are there any other
people in this house, Toby?

439
00:30:09,349 --> 00:30:10,433
Er, none.

440
00:30:11,184 --> 00:30:15,104
Well then, hurry up and do
to the rest of the village

441
00:30:15,146 --> 00:30:17,982
what I just did
to this charming couple.

442
00:30:18,191 --> 00:30:21,653
You won't keep me waiting,
will you, Toby?

443
00:30:23,613 --> 00:30:24,614
[loud whizzing]

444
00:30:30,829 --> 00:30:31,913
[high pitch zap]

445
00:30:37,001 --> 00:30:39,504
[Sherry] Toby! Where are you?

446
00:30:39,712 --> 00:30:42,423
Sherry, go and hide
yourself in the forest.

447
00:30:42,590 --> 00:30:45,218
If you don't hide,
your brother-- [loud zap]

448
00:30:45,468 --> 00:30:48,137
will have to turn you
into a living puppet.

449
00:30:49,597 --> 00:30:53,476
[cries] Why are you doing to us?
Please, Toby, change Mother

450
00:30:53,518 --> 00:30:56,145
and Father back again.
Change them back.

451
00:30:56,688 --> 00:31:00,066
I'm sorry, Sherry, but I can't.
I don't know how.

452
00:31:00,316 --> 00:31:02,026
Only Lord Kuruku
has the power

453
00:31:02,026 --> 00:31:03,695
to change our mother
and father back.

454
00:31:04,195 --> 00:31:06,406
I can only follow
my master's orders.

455
00:31:07,782 --> 00:31:10,535
and so I must turn
all the villagers,

456
00:31:10,743 --> 00:31:13,162
people of my own kind
into living puppets!

457
00:31:13,746 --> 00:31:16,374
And in return
my master teaches me

458
00:31:16,374 --> 00:31:18,501
another little
bit of his magic.

459
00:31:19,627 --> 00:31:20,962
But some day Cheri,

460
00:31:21,254 --> 00:31:23,339
when I'm the greatest
magician in the world

461
00:31:24,632 --> 00:31:28,011
I will find the way
to repay you. I swear it!

462
00:31:28,553 --> 00:31:31,556
[turbulent music]

463
00:32:09,177 --> 00:32:10,637
[music ends]

464
00:32:15,808 --> 00:32:17,810
[casual music]

465
00:33:39,642 --> 00:33:41,310
[Cheri gasps and moans]

466
00:33:44,897 --> 00:33:46,899
[gasps and moans]

467
00:33:54,365 --> 00:33:56,117
Father! Mother!

468
00:33:56,534 --> 00:33:58,244
They both going away somewhere.

469
00:33:58,536 --> 00:34:00,747
They're all going away.

470
00:34:14,552 --> 00:34:16,554
[music crescendo]

471
00:34:25,938 --> 00:34:27,398
[Cheri panting]

472
00:34:28,066 --> 00:34:30,610
I can't tell which is father
and mother anymore.

473
00:34:31,069 --> 00:34:32,862
They're all going down
to the harbor.

474
00:34:33,196 --> 00:34:34,655
I wonder why.

475
00:34:35,490 --> 00:34:37,033
[Cheri] Let's follow them
and find out.

476
00:34:37,241 --> 00:34:38,242
[Unico] All right.

477
00:34:39,827 --> 00:34:41,829
[music continues]

478
00:35:07,105 --> 00:35:08,773
[music ends]

479
00:35:12,944 --> 00:35:14,028
Wait for me!

480
00:35:24,205 --> 00:35:26,165
We've gotta get on that ship
with my parents.

481
00:35:26,791 --> 00:35:29,710
[Unico] I wonder
where they taking everybody.

482
00:35:30,711 --> 00:35:31,963
Nightmare Island.

483
00:35:32,171 --> 00:35:33,756
[Yamaneko] Nightmare Island,
huh?

484
00:35:33,965 --> 00:35:36,592
I heard bad things
about that place.

485
00:35:40,471 --> 00:35:41,472
[Cheri gasps]

486
00:35:42,098 --> 00:35:44,225
[Cheri and Unico moan]

487
00:35:44,642 --> 00:35:45,643
[Cheri and Unico gasp]

488
00:35:52,483 --> 00:35:54,944
Why is your boss wanna
carry all these things

489
00:35:54,944 --> 00:35:57,238
to Nightmare Island for? Huh?

490
00:35:59,240 --> 00:36:01,075
You'll find out
when we get there.

491
00:36:18,176 --> 00:36:20,261
I wonder
where this ship is going.

492
00:36:20,595 --> 00:36:23,306
I don't know but I hope
it gets there soon.

493
00:36:24,849 --> 00:36:26,392
-[Unico] Whoa!
-[Cheri gasps]

494
00:36:26,642 --> 00:36:28,477
Is Nightmare Island far?

495
00:36:29,770 --> 00:36:31,022
No, not far at all.

496
00:36:31,522 --> 00:36:32,815
You can see it already.
[lightning strikes]

497
00:36:33,608 --> 00:36:34,692
[Yamaneko gasps]

498
00:36:36,235 --> 00:36:38,237
[anticipatory music]

499
00:37:24,951 --> 00:37:26,953
[music ends]

500
00:37:27,536 --> 00:37:30,289
[casual music]
[Yamaneko sighs]

501
00:37:31,749 --> 00:37:34,252
[Yamaneko sighs and laughs]

502
00:37:57,942 --> 00:38:00,278
-Hurry Unico! Hurry!
-I'm coming!

503
00:38:00,861 --> 00:38:03,823
Wow, I never seen anything
like this place.

504
00:38:08,577 --> 00:38:09,662
[Yamaneko] Huh? What?

505
00:38:10,204 --> 00:38:12,498
Well, I'll be a monkey's uncle.

506
00:38:14,125 --> 00:38:16,294
We've got to try
and find Lord Kuruku.

507
00:38:16,294 --> 00:38:18,421
Are you sure you know
what you're doing?

508
00:38:18,587 --> 00:38:19,588
[Yamaneko]

509
00:38:24,343 --> 00:38:25,428
Where they go?

510
00:38:25,720 --> 00:38:27,722
Where? Ah,
there they are! [grunts]

511
00:38:31,267 --> 00:38:32,893
[grunting]

512
00:38:33,602 --> 00:38:34,812
[screams]

513
00:38:44,613 --> 00:38:46,574
[music ends]

514
00:38:46,949 --> 00:38:48,284
Excuse me!

515
00:38:48,617 --> 00:38:52,288
Does anybody know where we can
find Lord Kuruku?

516
00:38:52,621 --> 00:38:55,416
-[Unico and Cheri scream]
-[monster screams and grunts]

517
00:38:56,167 --> 00:38:57,877
-[Cheri] Run!
-[Unico screams]

518
00:38:58,461 --> 00:38:59,587
[monster grunts]

519
00:38:59,795 --> 00:39:01,464
[tense music]

520
00:39:01,589 --> 00:39:03,174
-[Cheri moaning]
-[monster grunting]

521
00:39:04,258 --> 00:39:05,801
[monster screams]

522
00:39:06,302 --> 00:39:08,471
Oh no! What is it?

523
00:39:08,637 --> 00:39:11,140
I don't know
and I don't wanna find out!

524
00:39:11,307 --> 00:39:13,851
-I think [indistinct] smell.
-[monster screams]

525
00:39:18,481 --> 00:39:19,565
[monster grunts]

526
00:39:20,566 --> 00:39:22,818
-[Cheri and Unico gasping]
-[monster screams]

527
00:39:25,237 --> 00:39:26,489
-[Cheri gasps]
-[Unico moans]

528
00:39:27,531 --> 00:39:29,533
[Cheri and Unico
panting and moaning]

529
00:39:33,245 --> 00:39:35,247
[Cheri and Unico scream]
[music ends]

530
00:39:36,457 --> 00:39:38,334
[monster screams]

531
00:39:40,044 --> 00:39:42,046
[Cheri and Unico scream]

532
00:39:44,632 --> 00:39:46,342
[Cheri screams]

533
00:39:47,051 --> 00:39:48,427
[Cheri and Unico sigh]

534
00:39:53,682 --> 00:39:55,684
[anticipation music]

535
00:39:59,063 --> 00:40:01,982
Oh! I have house guests I see.

536
00:40:02,650 --> 00:40:04,485
However did you
find your way in?

537
00:40:04,527 --> 00:40:05,694
[Unico] Lord Kuruku!

538
00:40:05,820 --> 00:40:08,155
Please, sir, I beg of you!

539
00:40:08,948 --> 00:40:10,074
You beg of me?

540
00:40:10,908 --> 00:40:13,702
Are you volunteering
to become living puppets?

541
00:40:13,786 --> 00:40:15,704
That's very charitable of you.

542
00:40:15,788 --> 00:40:17,540
Oh, you know
that's not what I mean.

543
00:40:17,873 --> 00:40:20,251
Turning people
into puppets is a wicked thing!

544
00:40:20,251 --> 00:40:21,961
You're a bad man!

545
00:40:22,586 --> 00:40:24,463
[Kuruku laughing]

546
00:40:28,217 --> 00:40:29,718
We'll aside from that,

547
00:40:29,844 --> 00:40:33,097
am I the sort of person you
like to expend time with, huh?

548
00:40:33,556 --> 00:40:35,182
Lord Kuruku you've got

549
00:40:35,224 --> 00:40:37,351
to return my mother
and my father!

550
00:40:38,185 --> 00:40:40,104
You're wasting your
time little girl

551
00:40:40,146 --> 00:40:42,481
and what's worse
you're wasting mine.

552
00:40:43,315 --> 00:40:46,735
Toby! Toby, come to me!

553
00:40:48,696 --> 00:40:49,905
I'm here master.

554
00:40:51,323 --> 00:40:53,868
I want you to deal
with these annoying pair

555
00:40:53,868 --> 00:40:56,287
of little trespassers Toby.

556
00:40:56,579 --> 00:40:59,039
- Huh? Cheri!
-Toby!

557
00:41:00,541 --> 00:41:02,835
I beg a favor of you
Lord Kuruku.

558
00:41:03,586 --> 00:41:06,881
My! This is a big day
for begging favors.

559
00:41:07,047 --> 00:41:09,717
-What it is?
-They're only children master.

560
00:41:09,842 --> 00:41:12,845
Please don't force me to turn
them into living puppets.

561
00:41:12,887 --> 00:41:15,806
Well then,
what is that you propose?

562
00:41:16,307 --> 00:41:17,850
As they're only children

563
00:41:18,309 --> 00:41:20,603
let me turn them
into toys master.

564
00:41:21,604 --> 00:41:24,440
Fine, fine, just get rid
of the little brats.

565
00:41:24,815 --> 00:41:25,900
Thank you master.

566
00:41:27,735 --> 00:41:29,612
[Cheri gasping and moaning]

567
00:41:32,990 --> 00:41:34,200
[Cheri gasps]

568
00:41:37,786 --> 00:41:39,622
Cheri, why didn't you listen

569
00:41:39,663 --> 00:41:41,332
when I told you to hide
in the forest?

570
00:41:41,373 --> 00:41:44,335
This is the weirdest
looking toy I ever saw.

571
00:41:46,045 --> 00:41:47,505
[monster rattles]

572
00:41:52,760 --> 00:41:53,802
Forgive me Cheri.

573
00:41:54,637 --> 00:41:57,014
But you see,
I know the magic for toys.

574
00:41:57,306 --> 00:41:58,432
Soon I'll change back

575
00:41:58,474 --> 00:42:00,351
and carry you away
from this island.

576
00:42:00,976 --> 00:42:03,229
[Yamaneko] Yeah, but doesn't
mean you have to do it

577
00:42:03,229 --> 00:42:04,730
for this little run too.

578
00:42:05,689 --> 00:42:07,024
[magic sound]

579
00:42:07,775 --> 00:42:08,776
[both gasp]

580
00:42:15,324 --> 00:42:17,326
[suspenseful music]

581
00:42:22,122 --> 00:42:24,208
All right my little toys,

582
00:42:24,750 --> 00:42:27,086
I'm in the mood to be amused.

583
00:42:29,380 --> 00:42:31,382
[cheerful music]

584
00:42:41,433 --> 00:42:42,977
[Kuruku screams] Oh!

585
00:42:49,942 --> 00:42:50,943
[Kuruku screams]

586
00:42:52,444 --> 00:42:53,946
[Kuruku grunting]

587
00:42:58,367 --> 00:42:59,410
[Kuruku grunts]

588
00:43:52,296 --> 00:43:53,339
[Kuruku gasps]

589
00:43:54,131 --> 00:43:56,884
Stop, stop, get back everyone!

590
00:43:58,886 --> 00:44:00,721
[music ends]

591
00:44:01,555 --> 00:44:03,807
Toby, shouldn't you be at work?

592
00:44:03,974 --> 00:44:05,851
-Yes master.
-You're not lying at me,

593
00:44:05,893 --> 00:44:06,894
are you?

594
00:44:07,770 --> 00:44:09,772
[casual music]

595
00:44:35,255 --> 00:44:38,592
Huh? What? They're joints
made out of living puppets.

596
00:44:39,009 --> 00:44:40,386
[screams] Hup-Hup!

597
00:44:42,262 --> 00:44:44,264
[music continues]

598
00:44:56,860 --> 00:44:57,945
I don't believe it!

599
00:44:57,986 --> 00:45:01,532
The walls are getting
higher and higher. Wow!

600
00:45:02,074 --> 00:45:06,203
[Kuruku laughing]
Better and better!

601
00:45:06,662 --> 00:45:09,832
The greatest magic
castle in the world

602
00:45:09,915 --> 00:45:12,418
and it's mine. [laughing]

603
00:45:14,503 --> 00:45:16,255
Nothing can stop me.

604
00:45:16,463 --> 00:45:19,758
Higher and higher
until its walls are made up

605
00:45:19,800 --> 00:45:21,635
with every living creature

606
00:45:21,635 --> 00:45:23,762
on the face of the earth.
[laughing]

607
00:45:36,942 --> 00:45:38,360
[music ends]

608
00:46:03,093 --> 00:46:05,095
[anticipation music]

609
00:46:06,680 --> 00:46:08,682
[monster screams]

610
00:46:13,061 --> 00:46:15,063
[monster screams]

611
00:46:17,816 --> 00:46:19,193
[music ends]

612
00:46:21,278 --> 00:46:23,322
[melodic music]

613
00:46:33,791 --> 00:46:36,001
[Cheri and Unico gasping]

614
00:46:41,089 --> 00:46:43,258
-Toby!
-And now I have an appointment

615
00:46:43,300 --> 00:46:45,344
to keep in the Valley
of the Demons.

616
00:46:45,594 --> 00:46:46,845
The Valley of the Demons?

617
00:46:47,012 --> 00:46:48,597
-What's that?
-I must go!

618
00:46:48,931 --> 00:46:52,267
No Toby, stop! You have to save
our mother and father.

619
00:46:52,476 --> 00:46:54,102
Come back here!

620
00:46:55,479 --> 00:46:56,522
Toby!

621
00:46:56,814 --> 00:46:59,650
What about our mother
and father?

622
00:47:02,277 --> 00:47:03,362
[Unico] He's gone.

623
00:47:04,196 --> 00:47:06,490
Where is
this Valley of the Demons?

624
00:47:06,990 --> 00:47:08,325
Oh, no!

625
00:47:08,784 --> 00:47:11,870
He's going there to turn
all them into living puppets.

626
00:47:12,871 --> 00:47:14,915
-Come on, Unico.
-Where to?

627
00:47:15,415 --> 00:47:16,917
We've got to go there too.

628
00:47:17,292 --> 00:47:18,752
The Valley of the Demons?

629
00:47:19,461 --> 00:47:20,838
We have to stop Toby.

630
00:47:21,380 --> 00:47:22,589
We have to warn the demons

631
00:47:22,589 --> 00:47:24,967
before they're all turned
into living puppets.

632
00:47:26,176 --> 00:47:28,720
[Unico grunting and moaning]

633
00:47:28,929 --> 00:47:31,223
Do we have to? [moans]

634
00:47:36,311 --> 00:47:38,313
[chaotic music]

635
00:47:49,575 --> 00:47:51,118
[music ends]

636
00:47:52,244 --> 00:47:54,246
[silence]

637
00:47:56,123 --> 00:47:58,417
[tense music]

638
00:48:13,140 --> 00:48:15,142
[music ends]

639
00:48:16,310 --> 00:48:18,312
[Cheri panting]

640
00:48:22,900 --> 00:48:26,278
-Hello! Is anybody home?
-Hello!

641
00:48:26,612 --> 00:48:27,863
It's so quiet.

642
00:48:28,113 --> 00:48:29,573
[sighs] Hello?

643
00:48:32,159 --> 00:48:35,203
[Cheri and Unico screaming]

644
00:48:39,291 --> 00:48:41,084
[Unico] Oh!
Who turned out the light?

645
00:48:41,168 --> 00:48:42,794
[Cheri] Unico, where are you?

646
00:48:43,128 --> 00:48:44,338
[Unico grunting]

647
00:48:44,588 --> 00:48:46,006
-[Unico grunts]
-What's wrong, Unico?

648
00:48:46,173 --> 00:48:47,633
[Unico grunts] Be
quiet for a minute,

649
00:48:47,799 --> 00:48:49,176
I'm trying to light up.

650
00:48:49,801 --> 00:48:50,761
[Cheri gasps]

651
00:48:52,429 --> 00:48:53,764
I can't believe it!

652
00:48:54,389 --> 00:48:57,851
-[Unico struggling grunts]
-[Cheri gasps]

653
00:48:58,310 --> 00:48:59,811
That's wonderful, Unico!

654
00:48:59,853 --> 00:49:03,023
I had no idea you could do
anything like that.

655
00:49:03,440 --> 00:49:06,735
[struggling grunts] I have
to work at it or it goes out.

656
00:49:07,694 --> 00:49:09,321
[Cheri] Is anybody here?

657
00:49:11,698 --> 00:49:13,742
It looks like they've all gone.

658
00:49:14,326 --> 00:49:16,370
Toby must've turned
them into puppets

659
00:49:16,411 --> 00:49:17,621
and taken them away.

660
00:49:18,956 --> 00:49:20,540
[crying in the distance]

661
00:49:21,625 --> 00:49:22,626
Listen!

662
00:49:23,043 --> 00:49:25,462
-What? What is it?
-[Unico hushes]

663
00:49:25,963 --> 00:49:27,172
-I hear something.
-[crying in the distance]

664
00:49:29,508 --> 00:49:30,842
It's over there!

665
00:49:31,593 --> 00:49:33,720
What do you think it could be?

666
00:49:36,848 --> 00:49:38,600
[Unico] It sounds like crying.

667
00:49:39,101 --> 00:49:40,560
But who could be crying.

668
00:49:40,852 --> 00:49:42,854
[crying in the distance]

669
00:49:43,063 --> 00:49:44,940
[Cheri] Hello! Who's there?

670
00:49:45,565 --> 00:49:47,109
[Unico] Oh! Here they are.

671
00:49:48,235 --> 00:49:50,195
[Cheri] Those are baby demons.

672
00:49:51,947 --> 00:49:53,991
So he wasn't able
to find you, huh?

673
00:49:54,282 --> 00:49:56,243
What happen to your parents?

674
00:49:56,493 --> 00:49:59,663
[all crying and moaning]

675
00:50:00,872 --> 00:50:03,625
He took all the mothers
and fathers away.

676
00:50:06,461 --> 00:50:09,047
We all hid down
here in this hole

677
00:50:09,297 --> 00:50:10,799
and now we are alone.

678
00:50:11,800 --> 00:50:13,093
[all moaning]

679
00:50:13,135 --> 00:50:15,637
It was my brother
who did this to you.

680
00:50:16,138 --> 00:50:18,557
Oh, forgive me! [crying]

681
00:50:19,016 --> 00:50:21,351
[all sobbing and screaming]

682
00:50:38,118 --> 00:50:39,661
Stop it everyone!

683
00:50:39,911 --> 00:50:43,915
Oh! When you cry
like that it makes me--

684
00:50:44,249 --> 00:50:46,668
[moaning and sobbing]

685
00:50:48,920 --> 00:50:50,130
[Unico] Oh!

686
00:50:54,134 --> 00:50:55,427
[yawns]

687
00:51:05,854 --> 00:51:08,065
Oh, please stop it!

688
00:51:08,899 --> 00:51:11,109
Stop crying, oh!

689
00:51:12,944 --> 00:51:14,071
I'm so sorry!

690
00:51:14,529 --> 00:51:16,782
I promise I'll bring
your parents back to you.

691
00:51:17,199 --> 00:51:19,618
Wherever they are,
I'll bring them back.

692
00:51:20,660 --> 00:51:21,745
I promise.

693
00:51:22,579 --> 00:51:24,247
How are you going to do that?

694
00:51:24,581 --> 00:51:27,751
We have no idea
how to fight Kuruku’s magic.

695
00:51:28,794 --> 00:51:31,630
There must be someone,
somewhere who would know.

696
00:51:31,963 --> 00:51:35,634
The Sphinx who knows everything
would probably know that too.

697
00:51:35,759 --> 00:51:37,594
The what that knows everything?

698
00:51:38,136 --> 00:51:39,888
Of course she'd know!

699
00:51:40,388 --> 00:51:41,389
Hey listen,

700
00:51:41,389 --> 00:51:44,434
if anybody know how to fight
his magic the Sphinx would.

701
00:51:45,060 --> 00:51:47,562
Well then,
where's exactly is the Sphinx

702
00:51:47,604 --> 00:51:48,980
who knows everything?

703
00:51:49,815 --> 00:51:51,608
-[demon 1 grunts]
-[Unico] Hey!

704
00:51:51,775 --> 00:51:53,360
Stop it! Let me go.

705
00:51:53,568 --> 00:51:54,611
[demon 1 grunts]

706
00:51:54,611 --> 00:51:57,280
-This is serious business you--
-[demon 1 grunts]

707
00:51:57,614 --> 00:52:00,367
Oh! Cut it up!
What's wrong with you?

708
00:52:01,409 --> 00:52:03,662
Cheri, we've got
to find this Sphinx,

709
00:52:03,662 --> 00:52:06,164
she's the only chance
that we've got.

710
00:52:06,748 --> 00:52:08,834
She's over there.

711
00:52:08,834 --> 00:52:10,502
You don't have far to go!

712
00:52:10,961 --> 00:52:12,796
We'll go and see the Sphinx

713
00:52:13,213 --> 00:52:16,341
and I promise we'll bring
your parents back to you.

714
00:52:16,758 --> 00:52:18,051
Don't worry!

715
00:52:19,344 --> 00:52:20,971
[Unico] We'll be back soon.

716
00:52:21,847 --> 00:52:23,682
So be brave!

717
00:52:24,599 --> 00:52:27,185
And don't cry!

718
00:52:30,605 --> 00:52:33,108
Mama! Mama!

719
00:52:33,859 --> 00:52:38,029
Mama! Mama! Mama!

720
00:52:40,824 --> 00:52:44,870
[all crying] Mama! Mama!

721
00:52:55,422 --> 00:52:57,424
[wind blowing]

722
00:53:00,427 --> 00:53:02,470
Unico, forgive me.

723
00:53:03,221 --> 00:53:06,141
I know I should never have
to drag you into all this.

724
00:53:06,975 --> 00:53:09,936
[sighs] Where do you think
the Sphinx could be?

725
00:53:11,730 --> 00:53:14,733
[Cheri] How could anyone
live in a place like this?

726
00:53:14,774 --> 00:53:15,775
[Unico grunts]

727
00:53:17,694 --> 00:53:19,154
Come on, Cheri.

728
00:53:19,738 --> 00:53:21,740
You're right,
we have to find her.

729
00:53:22,365 --> 00:53:25,410
For my mother and father sake.

730
00:53:26,369 --> 00:53:27,954
But I'm so tired.

731
00:53:29,664 --> 00:53:30,790
So tired.

732
00:53:32,417 --> 00:53:33,418
[Cheri moans]

733
00:53:36,087 --> 00:53:38,256
[Unico moaning]

734
00:53:39,549 --> 00:53:40,884
I can't go...

735
00:53:42,844 --> 00:53:45,513
-...much further.
-Who goes there?

736
00:53:45,722 --> 00:53:48,683
Who dares trespass on my desert?

737
00:53:49,893 --> 00:53:50,977
Go away!

738
00:53:52,062 --> 00:53:53,521
Hey, answer me!

739
00:53:54,898 --> 00:53:56,316
Are you two all right?

740
00:53:57,108 --> 00:53:58,109
[Mars worries]

741
00:53:58,693 --> 00:54:00,737
[emotional music]

742
00:54:02,906 --> 00:54:04,866
I've never seen anything
like you.

743
00:54:04,908 --> 00:54:05,909
What are you?

744
00:54:06,743 --> 00:54:07,744
[Mars grunts]

745
00:54:08,703 --> 00:54:10,497
[grunts] Huh!

746
00:54:10,789 --> 00:54:13,375
I'm not so sure
you're even worth to saving.

747
00:54:13,959 --> 00:54:15,001
[Mars sighs]

748
00:54:16,586 --> 00:54:20,548
[grunting] This one
is more like it!

749
00:54:20,632 --> 00:54:25,095
I'll be more than happy
to save your life. [laughing]

750
00:54:26,638 --> 00:54:29,766
Hmm, so you came all this way

751
00:54:29,766 --> 00:54:32,352
into the desert just
to see the Sphinx, huh?

752
00:54:32,852 --> 00:54:34,729
Yes, we got to see her.

753
00:54:34,980 --> 00:54:37,941
But she could be anywhere.
Can you help us?

754
00:54:38,692 --> 00:54:40,860
You see,
the Sphinx is my mother.

755
00:54:41,027 --> 00:54:44,656
But she's out visiting friends,
so I'm in charge.

756
00:54:44,781 --> 00:54:47,575
Oh, so you mean
the Sphinx isn't even here?

757
00:54:48,493 --> 00:54:50,704
And after we've come
all this way.

758
00:54:50,787 --> 00:54:52,122
Don't look so depressed,

759
00:54:52,622 --> 00:54:56,668
anything you wanna know
just ask me, I know everything!

760
00:54:57,752 --> 00:55:00,672
Do you know how to fight
Kuruku's magic powers?

761
00:55:00,880 --> 00:55:02,465
Kuruku? What's that?

762
00:55:02,841 --> 00:55:05,760
Anyway I'm not expected
to know about magic yet.

763
00:55:05,885 --> 00:55:07,554
Ask me something simpler.

764
00:55:07,595 --> 00:55:09,180
We’re in trouble Cheri.

765
00:55:09,889 --> 00:55:10,890
[Cheri moans]

766
00:55:12,225 --> 00:55:14,185
Oh, wait a minute!

767
00:55:14,394 --> 00:55:16,146
I bet the great Trojan Horse

768
00:55:16,187 --> 00:55:19,065
will be able to help
you fight this guy magic powers.

769
00:55:19,524 --> 00:55:23,361
My mother said that he knows
almost as much she does.

770
00:55:24,154 --> 00:55:25,280
The Trojan Horse?

771
00:55:26,531 --> 00:55:29,617
You got it! The Trojan Horse
at the End of the Earth!

772
00:55:30,785 --> 00:55:32,787
[blowing wind]

773
00:55:33,663 --> 00:55:35,623
But listen, the End of the Earth

774
00:55:35,623 --> 00:55:38,918
is a long, long,
long way from here.

775
00:55:41,379 --> 00:55:42,714
But that's where you find him.

776
00:55:44,841 --> 00:55:46,718
[Cheri] Could he really be
the one to tell me

777
00:55:46,718 --> 00:55:48,720
how to get my mother
and father back?

778
00:55:48,970 --> 00:55:50,680
But nobody is ever been able

779
00:55:50,722 --> 00:55:52,182
to make it
to the End of the Earth.

780
00:55:52,724 --> 00:55:55,185
Hey! Where do you think
you're going?

781
00:55:55,727 --> 00:55:59,064
[grunts] I tell you,
you're crazy!

782
00:55:59,898 --> 00:56:03,068
Hey, do you think you can just
walk to the End of the Earth?

783
00:56:03,318 --> 00:56:05,862
They're nuts. Hey, stop!

784
00:56:07,614 --> 00:56:10,784
[Mars sighs] Hey!

785
00:56:11,493 --> 00:56:14,788
Come back! You'll never make it!

786
00:56:15,288 --> 00:56:17,290
You can walk for years,
and years,

787
00:56:17,332 --> 00:56:20,377
and years and still not
even get close to it.

788
00:56:20,585 --> 00:56:23,338
[Cheri] That may be,
but I have to try.

789
00:56:23,963 --> 00:56:26,007
-Unico!
-Yes, Cheri?

790
00:56:26,049 --> 00:56:28,134
This is where we go
our separate ways.

791
00:56:28,885 --> 00:56:31,930
[laughs] Our separate ways?
What do you mean?

792
00:56:32,055 --> 00:56:33,473
Just what she said bone head.

793
00:56:34,140 --> 00:56:37,227
Can't you see that the lady
is trying to tell you goodbye?

794
00:56:37,268 --> 00:56:40,855
Goodbye? But is that mean
that she's leaving me here?

795
00:56:41,398 --> 00:56:44,067
No! I won't stay here!

796
00:56:44,275 --> 00:56:46,569
I'm coming with you
to the End of the Earth!

797
00:56:48,571 --> 00:56:49,864
-Unico?
-[Unico] Hmm?

798
00:56:50,115 --> 00:56:52,283
Thank you for coming
along with me this far

799
00:56:52,617 --> 00:56:54,661
but now I'll have
to go all alone.

800
00:56:55,078 --> 00:56:57,664
-I can't take you with me.
-Why not?

801
00:56:58,331 --> 00:57:01,042
-[Cheri] Just because.
-[Unico] Because why?

802
00:57:01,084 --> 00:57:02,085
Unico...

803
00:57:04,421 --> 00:57:06,548
-Goodbye!
-Cheri!

804
00:57:07,549 --> 00:57:10,385
-Stop following me,
-Cheri, what's wrong with you?

805
00:57:11,553 --> 00:57:12,554
What's wrong?

806
00:57:13,888 --> 00:57:15,515
She doesn't like me anymore.

807
00:57:15,598 --> 00:57:16,891
-Oh yeah?
-That's right!

808
00:57:16,933 --> 00:57:19,102
She's living me behind,
isn't she?

809
00:57:19,853 --> 00:57:22,647
[Mars] Bone head, she not only
likes ya, she loves ya.

810
00:57:23,356 --> 00:57:24,399
No she doesn't.

811
00:57:24,566 --> 00:57:26,985
If she did,
she wouldn't go away and...

812
00:57:27,485 --> 00:57:29,487
leave me here. She wouldn't.

813
00:57:29,946 --> 00:57:33,491
Is because she loves you
that she's making you stay here.

814
00:57:33,783 --> 00:57:36,202
She doesn't want you
to have to suffer too.

815
00:57:37,162 --> 00:57:40,248
She's gonna find the End
of the World all by herself.

816
00:57:41,124 --> 00:57:44,294
-She's really something else.
-[sighs] You're right!

817
00:57:45,253 --> 00:57:46,254
Cheri!

818
00:57:49,299 --> 00:57:50,383
Wait Cheri!

819
00:57:50,967 --> 00:57:54,179
You do love me! You do!

820
00:57:54,971 --> 00:57:56,806
And I love you!

821
00:57:57,599 --> 00:57:59,309
I can help you Cheri!

822
00:58:00,226 --> 00:58:01,394
I can!

823
00:58:01,603 --> 00:58:03,605
[confidant music]

824
00:58:07,859 --> 00:58:10,361
What? What's happen
to the little guy?

825
00:58:10,653 --> 00:58:12,363
Hey slow down!

826
00:58:12,363 --> 00:58:15,325
Is that or you'll fly right
right of the End of the Earth!

827
00:58:16,701 --> 00:58:18,453
[Cheri stammers] I'm sorry,

828
00:58:18,453 --> 00:58:20,413
I couldn't take
you with me Unico.

829
00:58:21,456 --> 00:58:23,082
I'll miss you already.

830
00:58:23,791 --> 00:58:25,543
Oh Unico, goodbye.

831
00:58:26,920 --> 00:58:27,962
[Cheri gasps]

832
00:58:29,422 --> 00:58:32,300
Who are you? Are you taking
me to the End of the Earth?

833
00:58:33,968 --> 00:58:36,846
Hey wait a minute! Wait for me!

834
00:58:37,388 --> 00:58:40,892
As long as you're going that way
take me with you!

835
00:58:43,061 --> 00:58:44,103
[Mars screams]

836
00:58:45,563 --> 00:58:47,690
At this rate
we'll be there in no time.

837
00:58:47,732 --> 00:58:49,484
Oh no! If you here

838
00:58:49,484 --> 00:58:52,320
that means you let Unico
back there all alone.

839
00:58:53,029 --> 00:58:57,742
Unico? Oh I think
he's all right-whoa!

840
00:59:08,461 --> 00:59:10,964
Oh, what could've
happen to Unico?

841
00:59:14,509 --> 00:59:17,303
[music continues]

842
00:59:28,314 --> 00:59:30,483
Do we still have
a long way to go?

843
00:59:30,733 --> 00:59:34,445
A long, long way.
And I'm getting hungry.

844
00:59:35,071 --> 00:59:36,948
Unico and Toby,

845
00:59:37,532 --> 00:59:38,866
mother and father,

846
00:59:39,492 --> 00:59:41,202
I wonder what's happen to them.

847
00:59:41,786 --> 00:59:42,912
I'm so alone.

848
01:00:10,773 --> 01:00:12,775
[screams]

849
01:00:14,235 --> 01:00:15,445
We're almost there!

850
01:00:28,249 --> 01:00:30,251
[music ends]

851
01:00:31,586 --> 01:00:33,046
Is this the End of the Earth?

852
01:00:33,379 --> 01:00:34,380
You've got it!

853
01:00:34,547 --> 01:00:37,175
And I know just where to look
for the Trojan Horse,

854
01:00:37,258 --> 01:00:39,844
my mother told me once. Come on!

855
01:00:40,928 --> 01:00:42,055
Hurry up!

856
01:00:43,765 --> 01:00:44,807
Thank you!

857
01:00:46,726 --> 01:00:47,977
[Cheri and Mars gasp]

858
01:00:50,772 --> 01:00:53,274
[Cheri gasps] Unico it's you!

859
01:00:54,651 --> 01:00:57,987
I should've know that we never
could've been separated.

860
01:00:59,030 --> 01:01:00,657
-Thank you.
-I can't believe it.

861
01:01:00,698 --> 01:01:02,700
Okay, okay, let's go!

862
01:01:02,950 --> 01:01:06,162
Are you gonna stand there
all day holding him like that?

863
01:01:06,496 --> 01:01:07,538
Come on!

864
01:01:11,292 --> 01:01:13,836
Why is there is so much
old junk here?

865
01:01:14,128 --> 01:01:15,672
[Mars] Because it's
the End of the Earth.

866
01:01:17,173 --> 01:01:19,926
All the things that nobody wants
get washed up here.

867
01:01:20,593 --> 01:01:22,095
[Mars screams]

868
01:01:24,305 --> 01:01:27,725
Oh, look! Here comes
some more junk now, huh?

869
01:01:32,605 --> 01:01:36,192
[sighs] No wonder somebody
threw this away. [screams]

870
01:01:37,652 --> 01:01:40,113
-[Mars screams]
-How sad.

871
01:01:40,405 --> 01:01:42,782
This junk could've been fix up
almost good as new.

872
01:01:43,157 --> 01:01:46,577
So this is what happens
to all the things nobody wants.

873
01:01:47,203 --> 01:01:49,956
-But where is the Trojan Horse?
-I know!

874
01:01:54,377 --> 01:01:58,381
Hey, Trojan Horse!
Where are you?

875
01:01:58,923 --> 01:02:01,092
This certainly
isn't the Trojan Horse.

876
01:02:01,551 --> 01:02:04,053
-[object 1] You're a human!
-[Cheri gasps]

877
01:02:04,846 --> 01:02:05,847
Who said that?

878
01:02:05,847 --> 01:02:08,558
-[lantern] A human!
-[vase] Yes a human!

879
01:02:08,808 --> 01:02:11,352
-[carriage] A human?
-[object 2] A human!

880
01:02:11,602 --> 01:02:12,603
[drum] A human!

881
01:02:12,645 --> 01:02:14,981
Just like the ones
that threw us away!

882
01:02:15,356 --> 01:02:19,068
[all objects] It's a human!
A human! A human!

883
01:02:23,740 --> 01:02:26,284
All quit your bellyaching!

884
01:02:26,993 --> 01:02:28,786
All of you shut up!

885
01:02:29,871 --> 01:02:31,581
[Mars grunts]

886
01:02:31,998 --> 01:02:35,168
Oh, where could
the Trojan Horse be?

887
01:02:35,209 --> 01:02:37,044
- Was someone looking for me?
-[Cheri gasps]

888
01:02:37,545 --> 01:02:39,672
-Where are you?
-[Trojan Horse] Well, I...

889
01:02:39,756 --> 01:02:42,425
I'm right under you, young lady.

890
01:02:42,467 --> 01:02:44,177
[gasps] Pardon me!

891
01:02:44,719 --> 01:02:46,637
[grunts] Is that you?

892
01:02:46,846 --> 01:02:48,848
I'm the Trojan Horse.

893
01:02:49,390 --> 01:02:52,101
Wow! What a mess of a horse!

894
01:02:52,643 --> 01:02:54,771
[Trojan Horse] Am I really
that filthy?

895
01:02:55,354 --> 01:02:58,107
You bet you are.
You're disgusting.

896
01:02:58,316 --> 01:02:59,358
-Isn't it?
-Yep.

897
01:02:59,358 --> 01:03:01,235
[Trojan Horse] Well,
I'm not surprised,

898
01:03:01,277 --> 01:03:03,196
it's been over a thousand years

899
01:03:03,196 --> 01:03:06,157
since anyone bother
to give me a good cleaning.

900
01:03:06,616 --> 01:03:10,328
Oh, that's all right! If we
just dusty you off...[coughs]

901
01:03:10,995 --> 01:03:13,372
You'll be as good as new. See?

902
01:03:13,873 --> 01:03:15,792
[Trojan Horse] I thank
you, young lady.

903
01:03:16,626 --> 01:03:19,879
[sighs] I feel better already!

904
01:03:21,297 --> 01:03:24,550
I'd almost forgotten
what it was like to have

905
01:03:24,801 --> 01:03:26,969
someone take care of me.

906
01:03:27,553 --> 01:03:28,596
[Cheri] There you go.

907
01:03:30,473 --> 01:03:31,474
[coughing]

908
01:03:31,808 --> 01:03:35,436
Would you might terribly if we
asked you a question Mr. Horse?

909
01:03:35,978 --> 01:03:38,439
[Trojan Horse] It's about
Lord Kuruku, isn't it?

910
01:03:38,815 --> 01:03:41,192
Why don't you take a pick
in my eye young lady?

911
01:03:41,651 --> 01:03:42,693
In your eye?
[casual music]

912
01:03:43,319 --> 01:03:45,530
Then you already know
about Kuruku?

913
01:03:45,696 --> 01:03:48,699
[Trojan Horse laughs] You'd be
surprise that what I know

914
01:03:48,991 --> 01:03:52,370
and what I can reveal to you
when you look in my eye.

915
01:03:52,620 --> 01:03:54,956
-[all sigh]
-[Trojan Horse] Very well...

916
01:03:56,082 --> 01:03:58,751
I'll tell you
the story of Kuruku.

917
01:03:59,627 --> 01:04:03,381
Long, long ago
Kuruku washed up here

918
01:04:03,756 --> 01:04:06,926
just like all the others things
you see about you.

919
01:04:06,926 --> 01:04:08,553
[Mars] Look! It's a puppet.

920
01:04:08,761 --> 01:04:10,805
[Trojan Horse] Yes,
once upon a time

921
01:04:10,847 --> 01:04:12,932
Kuruku was a marionette

922
01:04:13,307 --> 01:04:15,810
but unhappily he fell
into the hands

923
01:04:15,852 --> 01:04:18,104
of some very bad people.

924
01:04:18,354 --> 01:04:19,856
[Unico] Bad people?

925
01:04:20,189 --> 01:04:23,109
[Trojan Horse] Yes.
A mean tempered old woman

926
01:04:23,150 --> 01:04:24,694
and a wicked magician.

927
01:04:24,986 --> 01:04:27,655
They mistreated Kuruku terribly,

928
01:04:28,030 --> 01:04:30,324
they pulled
and yank at his strings.

929
01:04:30,491 --> 01:04:32,785
And when they finally
became a tangled mess

930
01:04:32,827 --> 01:04:35,371
they simply threw him away.

931
01:04:36,831 --> 01:04:38,332
[Cheri] They throw him away?

932
01:04:38,374 --> 01:04:40,835
[Trojan Horse] As if he was
so much garbage.

933
01:04:41,085 --> 01:04:44,422
And after countless years
floating in the sea

934
01:04:44,630 --> 01:04:47,216
he washed up here
at the End of the Earth.

935
01:04:53,222 --> 01:04:55,892
-[Unico] Look a beam of light!
-[Cheri] What is it?

936
01:04:56,392 --> 01:04:58,728
[Trojan Horse] There's only
one spot in the land

937
01:04:58,728 --> 01:05:01,731
at the end of the Earth
where the sun shines.

938
01:05:02,106 --> 01:05:05,192
And then for only
a few moments every day.

939
01:05:06,110 --> 01:05:09,155
That is the spot
where Kuruku ended up.

940
01:05:09,780 --> 01:05:15,036
And after 200 or 300 years
of this a strange thing happen.

941
01:05:15,244 --> 01:05:17,580
[Cheri] He's beginning to move!

942
01:05:18,039 --> 01:05:19,165
[Trojan Horse] Just so.

943
01:05:19,874 --> 01:05:23,794
The light of the sun is full
of mysterious powers.

944
01:05:25,504 --> 01:05:28,966
But at the same time,
it woke him for his long sleep

945
01:05:29,133 --> 01:05:32,845
it candled in him a burning
hatred of humanity.

946
01:05:33,429 --> 01:05:36,807
For it was humanity
that it throw him away.

947
01:05:37,224 --> 01:05:39,310
And so one day,

948
01:05:39,310 --> 01:05:44,023
he left the land of the End of
the Earth in search for revenge.

949
01:05:51,572 --> 01:05:53,824
So how can we fight
Kuruku's magic?

950
01:05:54,075 --> 01:05:56,494
-[Trojan Horse] I don't know.
-[all] What?

951
01:05:56,994 --> 01:05:59,121
[Trojan Horse] I only know
that your courage

952
01:05:59,163 --> 01:06:01,749
and love are the best
weapons against him.

953
01:06:02,041 --> 01:06:04,752
[both] Huh?
Is that all you can say?

954
01:06:05,169 --> 01:06:06,879
That is all I can say.

955
01:06:07,546 --> 01:06:10,841
You must fight his evil
with your goodness.

956
01:06:11,050 --> 01:06:13,386
And you won't know
which is the stronger

957
01:06:13,427 --> 01:06:15,388
until the battle is over.

958
01:06:15,638 --> 01:06:17,306
Right, let's go find out!

959
01:06:17,515 --> 01:06:19,266
[Cheri] Thank you Mr. Horse!

960
01:06:19,517 --> 01:06:21,352
[Trojan Horse] Goodbye
my children.

961
01:06:22,144 --> 01:06:24,146
[confidant music]

962
01:06:33,906 --> 01:06:36,075
What's sort of a place
are we going to?

963
01:06:36,283 --> 01:06:38,035
It's called Nightmare Island.

964
01:06:38,703 --> 01:06:43,416
[cheers] That sounds
like my kind of a place.

965
01:07:03,644 --> 01:07:04,645
[Cheri] There it is!

966
01:07:05,104 --> 01:07:08,649
[Mars] Yeah? It doesn't look
all that scary. [moans]

967
01:07:21,829 --> 01:07:23,497
[music ends]

968
01:07:25,624 --> 01:07:27,668
Okay, so where's
this Kuruku fella?

969
01:07:27,668 --> 01:07:29,378
Come on, let me at him.

970
01:07:29,420 --> 01:07:31,130
Just let me at him, huh!

971
01:07:31,756 --> 01:07:34,133
Huh? Hey, I don't know

972
01:07:34,175 --> 01:07:36,302
but I think
maybe I've found him.

973
01:07:36,844 --> 01:07:38,429
[gasps] Is he already?

974
01:07:38,596 --> 01:07:40,473
-[monster grunts]
-Hey you big jerk,

975
01:07:40,514 --> 01:07:41,515
what a fat lip.

976
01:07:42,058 --> 01:07:44,643
[monster and Mars scream]

977
01:07:45,102 --> 01:07:46,854
[moans] Wait a minute!

978
01:07:47,104 --> 01:07:48,606
[Mars and Cheri scream]
[anticipatory music]

979
01:07:49,106 --> 01:07:51,692
-[monster screams]
-[Cheri and Mars screaming]

980
01:07:54,195 --> 01:07:56,530
[Mars panting]

981
01:07:56,947 --> 01:07:59,325
Hey I think we lost him.

982
01:08:00,034 --> 01:08:02,912
So hey, was that Kuruku guy?

983
01:08:03,329 --> 01:08:04,371
No, it wasn't.

984
01:08:04,497 --> 01:08:06,665
-[monster screaming]
-[Unico, Mars and Cheri scream]

985
01:08:13,631 --> 01:08:15,466
[monster grunts]

986
01:08:17,259 --> 01:08:19,428
-Quick, this way.
-Come on!

987
01:08:20,387 --> 01:08:23,641
-[Cheri panting]
-[Mars screaming]

988
01:08:24,350 --> 01:08:25,726
-[Mars] Hey!
-[Cheri gasps]

989
01:08:26,977 --> 01:08:29,355
[all screaming]

990
01:08:30,356 --> 01:08:32,358
[all panting]

991
01:08:33,567 --> 01:08:36,028
This ain’t my idea
of a good time.

992
01:08:41,909 --> 01:08:46,163
[Kuruku] Is never a moments rest
around here recently.

993
01:08:46,455 --> 01:08:48,290
Who is it this time?

994
01:08:51,085 --> 01:08:55,923
Why it feels two insufferable
brats I met not long ago?

995
01:08:56,298 --> 01:08:59,510
Why on earth they run
around you supposed.

996
01:09:00,928 --> 01:09:04,849
-[Cheri gasps]
-[Mars] Let's get out of here!

997
01:09:04,849 --> 01:09:07,143
-But where do we go?
-We stay here!

998
01:09:07,560 --> 01:09:08,686
Run for your lives!

999
01:09:09,103 --> 01:09:11,188
No, we got to stick together.

1000
01:09:11,939 --> 01:09:14,066
I may be mistaken,

1001
01:09:14,525 --> 01:09:16,694
but didn't I have you both...

1002
01:09:17,194 --> 01:09:19,196
-turned into toys?
-Yes.

1003
01:09:19,989 --> 01:09:21,532
I even danced for you.

1004
01:09:21,782 --> 01:09:23,325
-[Cheri gasps]
-[Kuruku laughing]

1005
01:09:23,826 --> 01:09:27,663
I think perhaps Toby is playing
a trick on me, hmm?

1006
01:09:27,705 --> 01:09:32,001
Please Kuruku, you can't keep
everyone as your puppet forever.

1007
01:09:32,585 --> 01:09:34,795
That's right,
you've got to turn them back.

1008
01:09:34,879 --> 01:09:36,422
-[Kuruku grunting]
-[Unico screams]

1009
01:09:36,463 --> 01:09:38,632
Why should I, little one?

1010
01:09:39,425 --> 01:09:41,177
Why you're try to frighten me?

1011
01:09:42,344 --> 01:09:45,890
Toby, I like a word with you!

1012
01:09:46,599 --> 01:09:47,975
Toby!

1013
01:09:50,060 --> 01:09:52,229
-Yes, sir.
-[Kuruku] Not you idiot.

1014
01:09:55,524 --> 01:09:57,818
Yes, Lord Kuruku,
you have need of me?

1015
01:09:58,444 --> 01:10:00,237
Explain yourself!

1016
01:10:00,821 --> 01:10:01,822
Cheri!

1017
01:10:03,032 --> 01:10:04,283
What she's doing here?

1018
01:10:05,701 --> 01:10:09,288
I've had enough!
How do I get out of here?

1019
01:10:09,955 --> 01:10:11,248
[Yamaneko and Mars grunting]

1020
01:10:12,791 --> 01:10:15,294
-[Mars screams]
-[Yamaneko grunts]

1021
01:10:16,921 --> 01:10:17,963
Who was that?

1022
01:10:18,255 --> 01:10:21,425
Let me out! Let me out of here!

1023
01:10:22,009 --> 01:10:24,762
[Kuruku] Well, Toby to bring
this game to an end

1024
01:10:24,803 --> 01:10:28,390
I suppose you should have to
turn them into living puppets.

1025
01:10:30,726 --> 01:10:31,769
Toby?

1026
01:10:32,853 --> 01:10:34,396
Did you hear what I said?

1027
01:10:34,980 --> 01:10:39,318
There's really no other option
open to us now, is there?

1028
01:10:39,985 --> 01:10:41,487
Toby!

1029
01:10:42,112 --> 01:10:46,659
I ordered you to turn them
into living puppets, now!

1030
01:10:48,035 --> 01:10:49,787
You forget that I am human too,

1031
01:10:50,537 --> 01:10:51,747
Lord Kuruku.

1032
01:10:52,206 --> 01:10:54,250
Yes, so you are!
[tense music]

1033
01:10:55,084 --> 01:10:56,919
And it's amazing to me

1034
01:10:56,961 --> 01:11:00,047
that I've never held
that against you.

1035
01:11:00,756 --> 01:11:02,007
I've been waiting for the day

1036
01:11:02,007 --> 01:11:03,968
when you turn me
into a puppet as well.

1037
01:11:05,177 --> 01:11:07,096
I think that day has come,

1038
01:11:07,346 --> 01:11:10,266
after all you're no
longer of any use to me

1039
01:11:10,307 --> 01:11:13,185
if you won't obey orders, Toby.

1040
01:11:13,435 --> 01:11:15,688
You leave me no choice.

1041
01:11:18,482 --> 01:11:21,860
-Run Cheri, run fast as you can!
-I won't!

1042
01:11:21,944 --> 01:11:24,405
Do you really think
you're match for me?

1043
01:11:25,072 --> 01:11:27,533
-How interesting!
-Run Cheri. [grunts]

1044
01:11:28,993 --> 01:11:30,244
I won't run!

1045
01:11:30,327 --> 01:11:33,872
No matter what you say,
I won't leave you, I won't!

1046
01:11:33,956 --> 01:11:36,959
You little fool.
This is no place for you.

1047
01:11:37,793 --> 01:11:40,671
[Toby grunting and groaning]

1048
01:11:41,463 --> 01:11:42,715
Very well master.

1049
01:11:43,799 --> 01:11:45,342
See how you like this!

1050
01:11:49,388 --> 01:11:52,391
[laughing] Somehow I believe

1051
01:11:52,391 --> 01:11:55,561
you have to do a lot better
than that. [laughing]

1052
01:11:55,936 --> 01:11:57,521
There's more
where that came from.

1053
01:12:10,909 --> 01:12:13,203
What? [grunting]

1054
01:12:16,582 --> 01:12:18,584
[Kuruku screams]

1055
01:12:22,296 --> 01:12:24,298
[tense music continues]

1056
01:12:29,136 --> 01:12:30,346
[Toby moans]

1057
01:12:32,598 --> 01:12:35,684
[Toby groaning and grunting]

1058
01:12:39,355 --> 01:12:40,356
[Toby sighs]

1059
01:12:41,023 --> 01:12:42,691
Toby! [gasps]

1060
01:12:42,983 --> 01:12:44,151
Toby!

1061
01:12:44,943 --> 01:12:46,779
[crying and moaning]

1062
01:12:47,738 --> 01:12:48,739
[gasps]

1063
01:12:53,118 --> 01:12:54,703
I don't want you to think

1064
01:12:54,745 --> 01:12:57,623
that I've forgotten you,
little girl.

1065
01:12:58,040 --> 01:13:00,084
I won't run away Kuruku.

1066
01:13:01,001 --> 01:13:02,211
But I want to know,

1067
01:13:02,836 --> 01:13:05,464
why do you have
to do such bad things?

1068
01:13:05,506 --> 01:13:07,883
Because that the only things
he can do.

1069
01:13:08,133 --> 01:13:10,052
He's never done
a good thing in his life.

1070
01:13:10,511 --> 01:13:13,097
Please Kuruku,
won't you turn everyone back?

1071
01:13:13,389 --> 01:13:14,681
Yeah, turn them back.

1072
01:13:14,848 --> 01:13:19,353
My, what a couple of courageous
little creatures you are.

1073
01:13:19,395 --> 01:13:21,647
Aren't you a least
frightened of me?

1074
01:13:22,689 --> 01:13:26,276
-Actually, I'm terrified of you.
-And so am I.

1075
01:13:26,819 --> 01:13:29,822
Marvelous,
that's the nicest thing

1076
01:13:29,822 --> 01:13:32,408
-anyone have said to me all day.
-And...

1077
01:13:32,783 --> 01:13:35,202
-there's something else.
-[Kuruku] Go ahead.

1078
01:13:35,411 --> 01:13:37,287
This is a terrible
life you're living

1079
01:13:37,329 --> 01:13:39,415
when frightening
people makes you happy.

1080
01:13:39,665 --> 01:13:43,877
I'm living a terrible life,
am I? [laughing]

1081
01:13:44,128 --> 01:13:46,588
You don't know how happy
you're making me.

1082
01:13:46,922 --> 01:13:49,216
Please don't stop now.

1083
01:13:49,633 --> 01:13:52,594
-It feels wonderful!
-Stop it please,

1084
01:13:52,636 --> 01:13:55,681
-you shouldn't frighten people.
-Leave her alone!

1085
01:13:56,098 --> 01:13:57,891
[Kuruku laughing]

1086
01:13:58,725 --> 01:14:00,394
How delightful!

1087
01:14:00,727 --> 01:14:02,604
And to think once upon a time

1088
01:14:02,646 --> 01:14:05,774
I had to hide
my hatred of humans.

1089
01:14:06,066 --> 01:14:08,902
I had to dance when they wanted
to me to dance.

1090
01:14:09,027 --> 01:14:11,488
And smile when they wanted
to me to smile.

1091
01:14:13,365 --> 01:14:14,700
But no longer,

1092
01:14:14,741 --> 01:14:17,953
times have changed and the shoe
is on the other foot.

1093
01:14:18,537 --> 01:14:20,414
Isn't now, hmm?

1094
01:14:21,957 --> 01:14:24,668
-Kuruku listen--
-[screams] Shut up!

1095
01:14:26,753 --> 01:14:29,506
No longer do I take orders
from humans.

1096
01:14:29,715 --> 01:14:31,633
Your time has come.

1097
01:14:31,633 --> 01:14:33,886
-Stop!
-No Unico!

1098
01:14:35,345 --> 01:14:36,805
Unico run!

1099
01:14:42,019 --> 01:14:45,189
Now I just have a little
cleaning up to do outside,

1100
01:14:45,189 --> 01:14:46,899
my day will be complete.

1101
01:14:50,777 --> 01:14:52,779
[silence]

1102
01:15:01,997 --> 01:15:03,916
[Unico grunting]

1103
01:15:05,042 --> 01:15:07,503
[struggling grunts]

1104
01:15:10,005 --> 01:15:13,091
Cheri! Cheri! [crying]

1105
01:15:15,886 --> 01:15:18,722
[Cheri laughs] Unico!

1106
01:15:19,932 --> 01:15:21,433
Is that you, Unico?

1107
01:15:22,059 --> 01:15:23,685
-[Unico cries]
- Unico !

1108
01:15:24,645 --> 01:15:26,772
[Unico crying]

1109
01:15:27,105 --> 01:15:28,649
Cheri.

1110
01:15:29,566 --> 01:15:31,985
[Cheri] Unico,
please forgive me.

1111
01:15:33,111 --> 01:15:36,073
I should never have brought you
to such an evil place.

1112
01:15:36,490 --> 01:15:38,033
Unico run!

1113
01:15:40,744 --> 01:15:42,162
[Kuruku laughing]

1114
01:15:44,122 --> 01:15:45,916
Huh? Kuruku!

1115
01:15:46,291 --> 01:15:48,293
[anticipatory music]

1116
01:15:58,595 --> 01:16:00,430
[Yamaneko screams]

1117
01:16:03,100 --> 01:16:05,811
-Kuruku!
-Stop it! [grunts]

1118
01:16:11,483 --> 01:16:14,319
Stay away from me,
I had about enough of this.

1119
01:16:14,486 --> 01:16:16,154
Huh? [screams]

1120
01:16:20,617 --> 01:16:21,952
What's the big idea?

1121
01:16:21,994 --> 01:16:24,037
Look what you've
done to my tail.

1122
01:16:25,163 --> 01:16:26,582
[screams]

1123
01:16:29,626 --> 01:16:30,669
[grunts]

1124
01:16:31,837 --> 01:16:33,672
[Kuruku laughing]

1125
01:16:33,880 --> 01:16:35,966
There, I think that takes care

1126
01:16:36,008 --> 01:16:38,176
of all the little
annoyances for today.

1127
01:16:38,218 --> 01:16:39,761
[Unico] Not quite Kuruku.

1128
01:16:40,220 --> 01:16:43,098
Who's that?
What a resilient little fellow.

1129
01:16:43,348 --> 01:16:45,726
You're not finished
until you taken care of me.

1130
01:16:46,602 --> 01:16:48,604
[tense music continues]

1131
01:16:52,441 --> 01:16:54,443
[monster screaming]

1132
01:17:06,622 --> 01:17:08,624
[monster screaming]

1133
01:17:18,634 --> 01:17:21,970
Kuruku is time
you let your puppets go.

1134
01:17:22,179 --> 01:17:25,891
You intolerable little
rotten muffin, how dare you?

1135
01:17:32,522 --> 01:17:33,523
[Unico screams]

1136
01:17:34,399 --> 01:17:35,901
[laughs] He's fast,

1137
01:17:36,026 --> 01:17:37,986
I haven't had this
much fun in years.

1138
01:17:39,446 --> 01:17:42,240
[moans] I don't what I can do.

1139
01:17:42,616 --> 01:17:45,202
Maybe if I just keep on running
I can tire him out.

1140
01:17:48,955 --> 01:17:52,250
No matter where you are
you cannot escape.

1141
01:17:53,251 --> 01:17:55,253
[Kuruku laughing]

1142
01:17:56,129 --> 01:17:57,214
[screams]

1143
01:17:59,174 --> 01:18:00,217
[Unico sighing]

1144
01:18:07,849 --> 01:18:11,478
-[Unico screaming]
-[Kuruku laughing and screaming]

1145
01:18:12,312 --> 01:18:15,649
-I've got you now! [laughing]
-[Unico screams]

1146
01:18:20,946 --> 01:18:22,072
[Unico moaning]

1147
01:18:22,864 --> 01:18:24,825
[Unico screams]

1148
01:18:27,369 --> 01:18:28,829
[grunts and moans]

1149
01:18:30,163 --> 01:18:32,249
There is nowhere left to go.

1150
01:18:32,416 --> 01:18:33,792
I let everybody down.

1151
01:18:37,129 --> 01:18:41,883
And so the curtain falls
you little pain in the neck.

1152
01:18:42,008 --> 01:18:43,009
[Unico screams]

1153
01:18:44,928 --> 01:18:46,263
[moans and screams]

1154
01:18:48,223 --> 01:18:49,266
[Unico screams]

1155
01:18:52,602 --> 01:18:53,895
[Kuruku sighs]

1156
01:18:56,273 --> 01:18:58,150
[Kuruku sighing]

1157
01:19:04,322 --> 01:19:05,574
[Kuruku grunts]

1158
01:19:06,324 --> 01:19:09,327
-[Unico sighs]
-[Kuruku] I'll kill you!

1159
01:19:29,347 --> 01:19:31,349
[silence]

1160
01:19:32,726 --> 01:19:35,228
[Kuruku laughing]

1161
01:19:35,520 --> 01:19:39,149
Well, that was certainly
very exciting. [laughing]

1162
01:19:40,066 --> 01:19:41,401
[Unico] Kuruku!

1163
01:19:42,903 --> 01:19:44,863
-[Kuruku sighs]
-Please Kuruku,

1164
01:19:44,863 --> 01:19:47,491
break the spell
and release all your puppets.

1165
01:19:47,532 --> 01:19:50,118
If you don't,
I'll be force to fight you

1166
01:19:50,118 --> 01:19:51,620
and I might have to...

1167
01:19:51,912 --> 01:19:54,289
destroy you
and I rather not do that.

1168
01:19:54,623 --> 01:19:57,584
Why you insignificant
little brat--

1169
01:20:01,505 --> 01:20:05,884
I am through playing
games with you!

1170
01:20:08,011 --> 01:20:09,054
[Unico grunts]

1171
01:20:13,600 --> 01:20:15,602
[anticipatory music]

1172
01:20:26,571 --> 01:20:28,031
How do you like that?

1173
01:20:28,448 --> 01:20:32,285
Now you have no place to run,
you've fallen in glue pot.

1174
01:20:32,828 --> 01:20:34,663
I don't plan on running anymore.

1175
01:20:35,038 --> 01:20:37,874
You leave me no choice
but to fight you Kuruku.

1176
01:20:38,250 --> 01:20:40,836
I'll struggle to hide my terror.

1177
01:20:41,294 --> 01:20:43,046
Prepare to die!

1178
01:20:44,214 --> 01:20:45,340
[Unico screams] Ya!

1179
01:20:46,466 --> 01:20:48,468
[tragic music]

1180
01:20:50,595 --> 01:20:52,556
[Kuruku screams]

1181
01:20:55,100 --> 01:20:59,145
-[Kuruku screams]
-[Unico moaning]

1182
01:21:04,734 --> 01:21:06,111
[Unico moaning and grunting]

1183
01:21:07,529 --> 01:21:11,032
I should've known I never
stand a chance against him.

1184
01:21:11,283 --> 01:21:13,535
[Kuruku screams and grunts]

1185
01:21:17,163 --> 01:21:18,874
What are you talking about?

1186
01:21:19,749 --> 01:21:21,167
This is more than a scratch.

1187
01:21:21,543 --> 01:21:24,337
But I had no idea
I hardly touched you.

1188
01:21:24,504 --> 01:21:25,881
I'm sorry.

1189
01:21:26,631 --> 01:21:30,135
[sighs] Why are you saying
that your sorry?

1190
01:21:30,510 --> 01:21:32,429
Why?

1191
01:21:33,680 --> 01:21:37,309
-Because I feel sorry for you.
-You feel?

1192
01:21:40,562 --> 01:21:42,522
What do you mean
you feel sorry for me?

1193
01:21:44,524 --> 01:21:47,193
I'm sorry
that you're full of... [grunts]

1194
01:21:47,903 --> 01:21:49,237
so much hate.

1195
01:21:52,073 --> 01:21:54,618
You think that all people
are your enemies

1196
01:21:54,659 --> 01:21:57,495
but that's only because
you've never had a friend.

1197
01:21:58,246 --> 01:22:00,832
Did you say 'a friend'?

1198
01:22:01,333 --> 01:22:03,501
I know how important
friends are.

1199
01:22:03,710 --> 01:22:06,254
-That's why I understand you.
-[Kuruku gasps]

1200
01:22:06,755 --> 01:22:07,923
Please, stop it.

1201
01:22:08,590 --> 01:22:11,426
The idea of me
being someone's friend...

1202
01:22:12,719 --> 01:22:17,057
it's making me feel
quite ill. [screams]

1203
01:22:18,683 --> 01:22:21,227
I know what happen
to you long ago.

1204
01:22:21,853 --> 01:22:24,522
I know that some people
treated you badly.

1205
01:22:25,065 --> 01:22:28,318
If you had a friend you'd know
that not everyone is like that.

1206
01:22:28,485 --> 01:22:30,028
You must be very lonely.

1207
01:22:30,320 --> 01:22:32,906
Lonely!

1208
01:22:33,114 --> 01:22:37,327
He says that I'm lonely!

1209
01:22:38,995 --> 01:22:41,539
But don't you understand?

1210
01:22:42,123 --> 01:22:44,250
I hate people!

1211
01:22:44,501 --> 01:22:46,044
I do! [grunts and cries]

1212
01:22:50,674 --> 01:22:51,675
[Unico grunts]

1213
01:22:52,550 --> 01:22:53,885
What's wrong Kuruku?

1214
01:22:53,969 --> 01:22:56,596
How can you be so cruel?

1215
01:22:56,721 --> 01:22:59,557
All this talk of friendship
and understand

1216
01:22:59,557 --> 01:23:02,686
is making me feel
all soft and gooey.

1217
01:23:02,727 --> 01:23:04,187
[screams]

1218
01:23:04,854 --> 01:23:07,691
I live only to hate humanity

1219
01:23:07,732 --> 01:23:10,318
and now you tell me
that I'm lonely,

1220
01:23:10,735 --> 01:23:12,445
that people are good.

1221
01:23:12,696 --> 01:23:14,698
Like a I need a friend.

1222
01:23:15,115 --> 01:23:19,452
Your words are melting my heart.

1223
01:23:20,161 --> 01:23:21,830
[Kuruku screams]

1224
01:23:22,664 --> 01:23:25,709
Kuruku don't worry
I'll be your friend, okay?

1225
01:23:26,042 --> 01:23:27,711
[Kuruku screams]

1226
01:23:28,420 --> 01:23:31,172
If you free all the puppets
from your magic spell

1227
01:23:31,297 --> 01:23:34,592
-I'll be your friend forever.
-[Kuruku screams]

1228
01:23:35,093 --> 01:23:36,344
That word again.

1229
01:23:36,720 --> 01:23:39,764
Who would ever want
to be a friend of mine?

1230
01:23:39,973 --> 01:23:41,182
Who?
[sad music continues]

1231
01:23:41,433 --> 01:23:44,019
Oh, wait Kuruku
don't be frighten.

1232
01:23:44,561 --> 01:23:46,980
Anyone can have a friend,
really.

1233
01:23:47,981 --> 01:23:50,859
It's too late for me I'm afraid.

1234
01:23:51,359 --> 01:23:53,319
-[Kuruku grunts and moans]
-Kuruku!

1235
01:23:55,488 --> 01:23:57,949
[Kuruku grunts and moans]

1236
01:23:59,159 --> 01:24:00,744
[Unico] What's happening?

1237
01:24:02,996 --> 01:24:05,165
[Kuruku] My hatred was
the only thing

1238
01:24:05,206 --> 01:24:06,666
that kept me alive.

1239
01:24:07,167 --> 01:24:10,086
You've taken it from me,
I have nothing left.

1240
01:24:10,712 --> 01:24:13,048
But for the first time
in my life

1241
01:24:13,423 --> 01:24:15,383
I can hardly say it...

1242
01:24:15,884 --> 01:24:17,635
I feel good!

1243
01:24:21,639 --> 01:24:23,641
[emotive music]

1244
01:27:00,048 --> 01:27:02,091
-[woman] Unico!
-What?

1245
01:27:02,342 --> 01:27:05,428
Did someone called me? [moans]

1246
01:27:08,056 --> 01:27:11,643
Unico my child it's time
to you to leave this place.

1247
01:27:11,935 --> 01:27:13,811
-Leave?
-Yes.

1248
01:27:13,853 --> 01:27:16,439
The gods will soon discover
what you've done here.

1249
01:27:16,856 --> 01:27:18,983
I must take you
some place far away

1250
01:27:18,983 --> 01:27:20,485
where they cannot find you.

1251
01:27:21,527 --> 01:27:22,654
But why?

1252
01:27:23,446 --> 01:27:25,531
Because that is your faith,
Unico.

1253
01:27:26,032 --> 01:27:27,116
Come.

1254
01:27:27,659 --> 01:27:29,661
[calm music]

1255
01:27:39,921 --> 01:27:42,715
May I at least
to say goodbye to Cheri?

1256
01:27:43,258 --> 01:27:44,842
She will never forget you.

1257
01:27:45,760 --> 01:27:48,137
Cheri, goodbye.

1258
01:28:01,442 --> 01:28:03,444
